{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2015}} {{Orphan|date=January 2015}} {{Infobox dot-com company | name = Rukkus | company_slogan = | owner = | logo = File:Rukkus.com_logo.png | company_type = Private company | foundation = New York City | area_served = Worldwide | location_city = New York City | location_country = United States | revenue = | homepage = [https://rukkus.com https://rukkus.com] | screenshot = | caption = | url = [https://rukkus.com https://rukkus.com] | registration = | advertising = | alexa = | website_type = Ticket Marketplace }}
'''Rukkus''' is a live entertainment [[search engine]] that explores 100+ [[ticket (admission)|ticket]] [[website|sites]], as well as their network of private [[brokers]], to pinpoint the lowest prices for concert, sports, and theater tickets.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Epperson|first1=Sharon|title=Co-working spaces are transforming how we work|url=https://www.cnbc.com/id/102170930#.|website=CNBC}}</ref> They figure out the best-valued ticket by using an analytical engine that compares a seat's distance from the action to the price of the ticket. Rukkus also shows stadium layouts for arena shows to allow visualization of your seat,<ref>{{cite web|last=Robehmed|first=Natalie|title=Meet Rukkus, The New Way To Buy Cheap Tickets|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2014/02/07/meet-rukkus-the-new-way-to-buy-cheap-tickets/|publisher=''Forbes''}}</ref> and allows users to search for specific events by city or interest.<ref name="Rebecca Grant">{{cite web|last=Grant|first=Rebecca|title=Rukkus launches advanced ticket search engine for finding live music near you|url=https://venturebeat.com/2013/11/25/rukkus-launches-advanced-ticket-search-engine-for-finding-live-music-near-you/|publisher=Venture Beat}}</ref>
The company launched its [[mobile app]]<ref>{{cite web | last=Keane | first=Jonathan | title=How to check out your next penthouse from your armchair | publisher=[[BBC News]] | date=May 24, 2016 | url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-36357474 | accessdate=February 17, 2017}}</ref> in February 2014; it was named one of the five best ticket finder apps by iMore<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kazmucha|first1=Allyson|title=Best ticket finder apps for iPhone: Rukkus, Applauze, SeatGeek, and more!|url=http://www.imore.com/best-ticket-finder-apps-iphone-rukkus-applauze-seatgeek-and-more|website=iMore}}</ref> and a "genuine leap forward with loads of epic potential" by [[iPhone]] Savior.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Basile|first1=Ray|title=What's Not To Love About The Rukkus Ticket App?|url=http://www.iphonesavior.com/2014/03/whats-not-to-love-about-the-rukkus-ticket-app.html|website=iPhone Savior}}</ref> The Rukkus app is free, and features 2 tap purchasing, as well as in-app [[music streaming]] and artist recommendations.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hirst|first=Arron|title=Rukkus: Tickets To Any Music, Theatre Or Sports Event, Right On Your iPhone.|url=http://www.razorianfly.com/2014/02/23/rukkus-get-tickets-for-any-musictheatresports-event-right-on-your-iphone/|publisher=RazorianFly}}</ref>
== History == The NYC-based startup was founded in 2011 by Manick Bhan, a [[Duke University|Duke]] graduate and former [[Goldman Sachs]] employee with a vision to create "the [[Kayak.com]] of the event ticket world".<ref name="Erin Griffith">{{cite web|last=Griffith|first=Erin|title=Rukkus launches its "Kayak for tickets" site with tickets from 100 different providers|url=http://pando.com/2013/11/25/rukkus-launches-its-kayak-for-tickets-site-with-tickets-from-100-different-providers/|publisher=Pando Daily}}</ref> Bhan is now working on Rukkus with fellow former [[investment banker]] (and co-founder) Joe Messineo, third co-founder Angela McCrory, and 7 other employees.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kallen|first1=Lauren|title=Find a good team, advises Rukkus founder Manick Bhan|url=http://www.wework.com/magazine/members/member-spotlight-good-team-rukkus-manick-bhan/|website=WeWork}}</ref> On July 24, 2018, [[TickPick]] acquired the majority of Rukkus assets for an undisclosed amount.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ampthemag.com/the-real/tickpick-purchases-second-set-of-assets-through-a-bankruptcy-with-rukkus-acquisition/|title=TickPick Purchases Second Set of Assets Through a Bankruptcy with Rukkus Acquisition|last=Mims|first=Taylor|date=July 24, 2018|work=Amplify|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180725111734/http://ampthemag.com/the-real/tickpick-purchases-second-set-of-assets-through-a-bankruptcy-with-rukkus-acquisition/|archivedate=July 24, 2018|accessdate=July 24, 2018|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref>
